  <source>Mansoura University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In conventional laparoscopic cholecystectomy, the cystic duct and artery are clipped by metal
      clips. we propose a new method in which the cystic duct is ligated and the cystic artery is
      cauterized. the investigators compare both methods.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
